  "text": "Rashidian et al. [CITATION_1] in 2013 found that the physicians graduated from America are more proactive and sensitive to discuss the sexuality with the patients. Also their study showed that Iranian-American Physicians' attitude towards taking a sexual history may be influenced by their place of graduation and place of births, possibly influenced by culture.",
